|Space Spiral
|style="text-align:center"|1965
|style="text-align:center"|Von Roll/Willie Buhler's Space Towers Company
|A {{convert|330|ft|m|sing=on}} tall [[Gyro tower]] gives riders a 360-degree view of the surrounding area. Space Spiral was the first amusement ride in the world to top {{convert|300|ft|m}}. Space Spiral features a distinctive two-level cabin, found only on a few early models. However, the second level hasn't been used for years.
