===Soak City===
{{main|Soak City (Sandusky, Ohio)}}
Opened in 1988, '''Soak City''' is Cedar Point's water park. It is adjacent to Cedar Point and requires separate admission. Guests must get their hands stamped to re-enter Cedar Point.<ref name="FAQ"/>

==Live entertainment==
===Venues===
* The '''Good Time Theatre''' is an ice-skating area in [[Celebration Plaza]]. It was formerly the ''[[List of former Cedar Point attractions#Defunct attractions|Cedar Point Cinema]]'', which housed an [[IMAX]] theatre before its conversion into the Good Time Theatre for the 2002 season.

* The '''Extreme Sports Stadium''' is a stunt stadium situated between [[WindSeeker]] and Wicked Twister. It was known as the ''Oceana Stadium'' from 1980<U+2013>1998 and ''The Aquatic Stadium'' from 1999-2007.

* The '''Celebration Plaza Stage''' is in Celebration Plaza in front of the [[Iron Dragon (roller coaster)|Iron Dragon]]. It was built for the 2012 season as part of [[Luminosity <U+2014> Ignite the Night!]] and replaced a giant screen used for Hot Summer Lights.

* The '''Red Garter Saloon''' is a stage located on the Frontier Trail.

* The '''Palace Theater''' is next to the Last Chance Saloon in Frontiertown.

* The '''Camp Snoopy Theatre''' is a small stage in [[Camp Snoopy]].

===Shows===
''All shows are about 25 minutes.''<ref name="Shows">{{cite news |title=Live Entertainment Shows|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/things-to-do/live-entertainment| accessdate=June 22, 2012}}</ref>

* '''Absolute Country''' is a country music and dancing show begun in 2012 in the Red Garter Saloon.

* '''All Wheels Extreme''' is a stunt show in the Extreme Sports Stadium. It features bikers and gymnasts who flip, dive and perform stunts. It was introduced in 2008.

* '''Charlie Brown's Funtime Frolics''' takes place in the Camp Soopy Theatre.

* '''Happiness is...Snoopy''' is an ice-skating show begun in 2012 in the Good Time Theatre.

* '''Jamming DJ's''' are DJ's who take requests from people waiting in line for the Millennium Force daily and for the Raptor on weekends during the summer.

* '''[[Luminosity <U+2014> Ignite the Night!]]''' is a show performed nightly beginning in 2012 on the Celebration Plaza stage.

* '''Peanuts' Celebration at the Point''' is a [[Peanuts]] show performed at 5pm daily on the Celebration Plaza stage.

* '''Snoopy's Sing-A-Long''' is a singing and dancing show in the Camp Snoopy Theatre.

* '''Summer Daze''' is a show in the Palace Theater that debuted in 2012.

==Fast Lane==
{{Further|List of Fast Lane attractions#Cedar Point}}
[[Fast Lane (Cedar Fair Entertainment Company)|Fast Lane]] is Cedar Point's "two line" queue system, introduced in 2012. For between $40 and $55, in addition to the standard admission charge, visitors receive a wrist band allowing them to bypass the "normal-wait" line and enter the "Fast Lane". The Fast Lane puts purchasers immediately at the front of the line at 16 of the most popular attractions. Unlike previous virtual queue systems, Fast Lane is not an "up the exit ramp" feature. Each attraction has its own Fast Lane entrance that merges into the normal line at the ride. A limited number of passes are sold each day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/what-s-new/fast-lane |title=Fast Lane |publisher=Cedar Point |date= |accessdate=April 10, 2012}}</ref>

==Awards/rankings==
===Awards===
Cedar Point won the [[Golden Ticket Award]] from ''[[Amusement Today]]'' for "Best Amusement Park in the World" in 2011 for the fourteenth consecutive year. The park has also placed in categories for "Friendliest Staff", "Best Outdoor Night Production" and "Best Halloween Event". Cedar Point won "Best New Ride of 2007" with the roller coaster [[Maverick (roller coaster)|Maverick]].<ref name="nguyen">{{Cite news|last = Nguyen|first = Janet|title = For 10th Year, Top Rating Gets to the Point|publisher = Sandusky Register|date = September 6, 2007|url = http://www.thepointol.com/news/2007/91.html|accessdate =October 15, 2007 |archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20071020184342/http://thepointol.com/news/2007/91.html|archivedate = October 20, 2007}}</ref>

===Rankings===
[[File:Maverick Cedar Point.jpg|thumb|right|205px|Maverick, added in 2007, Cedar Point's newest roller coaster. It received the "Best New Ride of 2007" award]]
The following steel and wooden coasters were ranked by ''[[Amusement Today]]'' in 2011:<ref>{{cite web|title=GTA 2011|url=http://www.goldenticketawards.com/pdfs/2011_golden_ticket_section.pdf|publisher=Amusement Today|accessdate=February 26, 2012}}</ref>

====Steel====
*[[Millennium Force]]: 1st
*[[Top Thrill Dragster]]: 9th
*[[Magnum XL-200]]: 10th
*[[Raptor (Cedar Point)|Raptor]]: 18th
*[[Maverick (roller coaster)|Maverick]]: 21st

====Wooden====
*[[Blue Streak (Cedar Point)|Blue Streak]]: 49th

Cedar Point has also won several IAAPA awards, including the Applause Award in 1996.<ref>{{cite web|title=Cedar Point wins Applause Award|url=http://business.highbeam.com/53/article-1G1-18904648/cedar-pt-big-winner-iaapa|publisher=Amusement Business|date=December 2, 1996 |accessdate=June 26, 2012}}</ref>

==Resorts==
Cedar Point owns and operates six resorts located either on park grounds or less than a mile away.<ref name="Resorts">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/places-to-stay| accessdate=April 15, 2012}}</ref> All facilities are non-smoking, and all Cedar Point Resort guests can enter the park one hour before it opens to the general public. Rides that operate during this early-entry session are: [[Iron Dragon (roller coaster)|Iron Dragon]], [[Maverick (roller coaster)|Maverick]], Midway Carrousel, [[Millennium Force]], Ocean Motion, [[Raptor (Cedar Point)|Raptor]], [[WindSeeker]] and [[#Planet Snoopy|Planet Snoopy Children's Area]].<ref name="Resorts"/>

===On-site resorts and campgrounds===
[[File:Sandcastle Suites Hotel.jpg|thumb|250px|right|The Sandcastle Suites Hotel]]

'''[[Hotel Breakers]]''', the oldest resort at Cedar Point, was built in 1905. The hotel has 650 rooms and suites and is the closest resort to Cedar Point and Soak City. In 1997, Hotel Breakers was renovated and expanded, doubling its size. Hotel Breakers has standard hotel rooms, suites with views of Lake Erie, Snoopy-themed rooms and Wi-Fi in the lobby, rotunda and conference center. It has three pools, beach access, a conference center, and five restaurants including [[T.G.I. Friday's]] and [[Perkins Restaurant and Bakery]].<ref name="Hotel Breakers">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Hotel Breakers|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/rides/Places-to-Stay/Hotel-Breakers-2-9-12-39| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

'''Sandcastle Suites''' is a hotel at the northernmost part of the peninsula that contains 187 suites. It has Wi-Fi in the lobby and guest suites, an outdoor heated pool and whirlpool, beach access, tennis courts, a shuttle to both Cedar Point and Soak City, and two restaurants <U+2012> the Breakwater Cafe and the Sand Bar.<ref name="Sandcastle Suites">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Sandcastle Suites|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/rides/Places-to-Stay/Sandcastle-Suites-2-9-12-04| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

'''Lighthouse Point''' contains 64 cottages and 40 cabins and is located along the west bank of the peninsula. The centerpiece of Lighthouse Point is the [[Cedar Point Light (Ohio)|Cedar Point Lighthouse]], which was built in 1862 and is the oldest existing structure on the peninsula. It has an outdoor pool and outdoor whirlpool spa, a shuffleboard court, a game room, and shuttle service.<ref name="Lighthouse Point">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Lighthouse Point|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/rides/Places-to-Stay/Lighthouse-Point-2-9-12-31| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

'''Camper Village''' is the only place at Cedar Point where it is possible to hook up an [[RV]] to water and electricity. Camper Village sites range from deluxe sites with electricity, water, sewer and cable to 112 electric-only sites. The Camper Village has the Camper Village Store, an outdoor pool, a shuffleboard court, a game room, a shuttle service on Cedar Point Peninsula, a dump station and laundry facilities.<ref name="Camper Village">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Camper Village|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/rides/Places-to-Stay/Camper-Village-2-9-12-39| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

===Off-site Cedar Point-owned resorts===
'''[[Castaway Bay (Sandusky, Ohio)|Castaway Bay]]''' is an indoor waterpark resort opened by Cedar Fair in November 2004. It has over {{convert|38000|ft|m}} of water slides, shops, and a wave pool. There are 237 guest rooms and luxury suites. Castaway Bay has five restaurants, including [[T.G.I. Friday's]] and Bay Harbor.<ref name="Castaway Bay">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Castaway Bay|url=http://castawaybay.com/| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

'''Breakers Express''', a sister resort to the '''Hotel Breakers''', is located one mile (1.6&nbsp;km) from Cedar Point and is the closest hotel to the peninsula. It opened in 2000 and includes 350 guest rooms. Breakers Express has an outdoor heated pool, outdoor whirlpool spa, game room, and Wi-Fi in guest rooms.<ref name="Breakers Express">{{cite news |title=Cedar Point Resorts - Breakers Express|url=http://www.cedarpoint.com/rides/Places-to-Stay/Breakers-Express-2-9-12-31| accessdate=May 21, 2012}}</ref>

==Popular culture==
Cedar Point has been mentioned in several movies, TV shows, and books:

* In [[Bob Greene]]'s book ''Be True to Your School: A Diary of 1964'', Greene and two friends, who all live in suburban [[Columbus, Ohio]], take a trip in August to Cedar Point.<ref name="Bob Greene book">{{cite news|url=http://www.popmatters.com/pm/feature/be-true-to-your-school-060222 |title=Bob Greene's book, Be True to Your School |accessdate=July 4, 2012}}</ref>
* In the movie ''[[Knute Rockne, All American]]'', Knute worked as a lifeguard on the beach at Cedar Point, where he and his college roommate Gus Dorais worked on the forward pass, which was first used in a scrimmage game on the Cedar Point beach.<ref name="Knute Rockne, All American">{{cite news|url=http://www.sanduskyregister.com/2008/may/15/marker-commemorate-rocknes-sandusky-connection |title=Knute Rockne, All American |date=May 15, 2008|work=Sandusky Newspapers, Inc.|publisher=SanduskyRegister.com|accessdate=July 4, 2012}}</ref>
* Characters in the movie ''[[Edge of Seventeen (film)|Edge Of Seventeen]]'' work at a restaurant at Cedar Point. Though the movie is set in the 1980s, the only shot featuring the park was filmed at a distance and clearly shows the Raptor, which was built in 1994.<ref name="Edge of Seventeen">{{cite news|url=http://touch.movieline.com/movieline/#!/entry/5-essential-coming-out-movies-in-honor-of-lgbt-history,4feb10db7af68a84dccdcdd1 |title= Edge of Seventeen |date=October 12, 2011 |accessdate=July 4, 2012}}</ref>
* The 2004 movie ''Close Encounters of the Fourth Kind: Infestation From Mars'' is set in Sandusky and contains numerous scenes set at the park. Cedar Point is integral to the movies's plot. Some Cedar Point executives appear in the movie in cameo roles. Employees and guests who were there on filming days appeared as extras in scenes involving large crowds throughout the park.<ref>{{IMDb title|0427077|Close Encounters of the 4th Kind: Infestation from Mars}}</ref>
* In [[Cinda Williams Chima]]'s book "The Warrior Heir," the main characters take a field trip to Cedar Point with their high school class.<ref name="Cinda Williams Chima book">{{cite news|url=http://www.coolcleveland.com/wiki/Newsletter/CoolClevelandKidsSummerReadingListOfLocalAuthors |title= Cinda Williams Chima book, The Warrior Heir |accessdate=July 4, 2012}}</ref>
* In an episode of the show ''[[8 simple rules]]'', Bridget ([[Kaley Cuoco]]) and Kerry ([[Amy Davidson]]) talk about going to Cedar Point to visit their father, Paul ([[John Ritter]]).<ref name="8 Simple Rules">{{cite news|url=http://www.amydavidsonfans.net/wordpress/8-simple-rules-season-1-episode-8-by-the-book/ |title=8 Simple Rules |accessdate=July 4, 2012}}</ref>
* In episode two of season one of [[Travel Channel|Travel Channel's]] ''[[Bert the Conqueror]]'', Bert takes the Foursome Fearsome Challenge in which he rides the four fastest and tallest coasters in the park in under an hour.<ref name="Travel Channel">{{cite news|url=http://www.sanduskyregister.com/sandusky/2010/jun/15/travel-channel-host-tackles-cedar-point-coasters|title=Travel Channel host tackles Cedar Point coasters|date=June 15, 2010|work=Sandusky Newspapers, Inc.|publisher=SanduskyRegister.com|accessdate=December 30, 2011}}</ref>
* In episode four of season two of [[Travel Channel|Travel Channel's]] ''[[Off Limits (TV series)|Off Limits]]'', [[Don Wildman|Don]] works on Mean Streak and Millennium Force with the maintenance crew.<ref name="Travel Channel Off Limits">{{cite news|url=http://www.tvguide.com/tvshows/off-limits-2012/episode-17-season-1/digging-under-manhattan-climbing-coasters-and-training-in-disaster-city/330830|title=Off Limits Episode: "Digging Under Manhattan, Climbing Coasters, & Training in Disaster City"|date=May 8, 2012|work=Tvguide.com|publisher=Tvguide.com|accessdate=May 12, 2012}}</ref>

